19/04/2005
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- Local media reports quoted KFOR Commander Lieutenant General Yves de Kermabon on Monday (18 April) as saying that troop levels would be boosted in Serb settlements.
Oliver Ivanovic, leader of the Serb Ticket for Kosovo and Metohija, says he asked de Kermabon for additional deployments during a meeting in Pristina Monday, following recent bombings and attacks on individuals.
Meanwhile, Slovakian Defence Minister Juraj Liska said Monday that his country is considering whether to increase its contingent in KFOR from the current level of 100.
The Czech Republic recently decided to raise its contingent from 400 to 600 soldiers.
(Politika - 19/04/05;
Tanjug, FoNet, B92 - 18/04/05)
